               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>
                           <p>
                              <material>Parchment</material>. </p>
                        </support>
                        <extent>56. <dimensions type="leaf" scope="all">
                              <height unit="mm">90</height>
                              <width unit="mm">73</width>
                           </dimensions>. </extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>Foliated in the bottom right hand corner of the recto pages. Due to a
                              confusion of the correct order of the gatherings (the fourth and sixth
                              gatherings were mixed up), the correct order of the manuscript is:
                              1-24, 41-48, 25-40, 49-56.</p>
                        </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>7 complete gatherings of 8 leaves (4 bifolia) each.</p>
                        </collation>
                        <condition>
                           <p>On fols <locus>17</locus>, <locus>18</locus>, <locus>20</locus>,
                                 <locus>21</locus>, <locus>22</locus> and <locus>24</locus> there
                              are holes or tears in the parchment. They are encircled with ink, and
                              appear to have existed before the parchment was written on. Fol.
                                 <locus>18</locus> was folded, and the outer bottom corner is cut
                              away.</p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="12">
                           <p>Written in long lines with twelve lines per page. Red majuscules and
                              pen-flourished red and green majuscules occur. There are rubrics in
                              red. Fols <locus>1r</locus> and <locus>56</locus> are/were originally
                              blank. </p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="sole" script="textualis">
                        <p>The manuscript is written in a Gothic bookhand.</p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>A note on fol. <locus>55</locus> reads: <q xml:lang="is">Hialpi mier <lb/>
                           gud ad ad <lb/>
                           <gap reason="illegible"/>
                        </q>, on the same leaf, some illegible invocations and scribblings are
                        found.</p>
                  </additions>
                  <accMat>
                     <p>The AM-slip reads: <q xml:lang="is">Margretar Saga. <lb/> Mariu gratur
                              (<foreign xml:lang="la">er sermo de dolore. Mariæ, cum <lb/> filium
                              Deum crucifi<lb rend="hyphenated"/>gi conspiceret. <lb/> Prosopopoeia
                              sub per<lb rend="hyphenated"/>sona Mariæ. <lb/> Precatio ad
                              Mariam</foreign>. <lb/> Þen<ex>n</ex>an<ex>n</ex> bækling feck <lb/>
                           eg 1708 af Pale <lb/> Jonssyni lgman<ex>n</ex>e <lb/> en<ex>n</ex>
                              han<ex>n</ex> af Sr Gud<lb rend="hyphenated"/>mundi Biarnasyne <lb/>
                           (prestz ad vestur<lb rend="hyphenated"/>hőps holum) ä Stad <lb/> i Hruta
                           firde. Sr <lb/> Gudmundur erfdi ep<lb/>ter fdur sin<ex>n</ex>,
                              en<ex>n</ex>
                           <lb/> Sr Biarne atte h<ex>an</ex>a, <lb/> þä Pall lgmadur <pb/> var hia
                              h<ex>onu</ex>m i ken<lb/>slu f<ex>iri</ex> 30. arum <lb/> Asmundur //
                           Sr Þorsteinn <lb/> i Vestur hops <lb/> holum Sr Þorb<ex>er</ex>gur <lb/>
                              k<ex>ir</ex>kiu p<ex>restur</ex> / <lb/> ä Holum <lb/> Sr Biarne i
                           vestur hops <lb/> holum.</q>
                     </p>
                  </accMat>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin notBefore="1525" notAfter="1550" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
                     <p>The manuscript was written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace>. <name
                           type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name> dated the manuscript
                        c. 1500 (<bibl>
                           <ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">Katalog</ref>
                           <biblScope unit="volume">II</biblScope>
                           <biblScope unit="pages">482</biblScope>
                        </bibl>), whereas <name type="person" key="SteKar001">Stefán Karlsson</name>
                        (pers.) dates fols 1v-26v, 28r-41r and 47v-55v to <origDate notBefore="1525"
                           notAfter="1550">the second quarter of the sixteenth
                        century</origDate>.</p>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>According to the similar accounts found in <ref type="ms" target="#AM04-0435-a-en">AM 435 a
                        4to</ref>, and on the AM-slips, the codex once belonged to the priest <name
                           type="person" key="BjaTho002">Bjarni Þorsteinsson</name>, then to his
                        son, also a priest, <name type="person" key="GudBja001">Guðmundur
                           Biarnason</name> of <name type="place">Staður</name> in <name
                           type="place">Hrútafjörður</name> and then the lawman <name type="person"
                           key="PalJon005">Páll Jónsson</name>. The note on fol. <locus>30v</locus>
                        in <ref type="ms" target="#AM04-0435-a-en">AM 435 a 4to</ref> reads: <q xml:lang="is">Margretar Saga.
                           <lb/> Mariugratur i.e.: <foreign xml:lang="la">Sermo sub personâ <lb/>
                              Mariæ, de dolore Illius, cum fili<lb rend="hyphenated"/>um Christum
                              crucifigi videret. <lb/> Precatio ad Mariam.</foreign>
                           <lb/> i litlu 16. blada forme. <lb/> Eg feck þen<ex>n</ex>an bækling
                           1708. af lg<lb rend="hyphenated"/>man<ex>n</ex>enum Ple Jonssyne.
                              en<ex>n</ex> hann <lb/> af Sr Gudmunde Biarnasyne  <lb/> Stad i
                           Hrutafirde. Sr Gudmundr <lb/> hafdi erft epter fdur sin<ex>n</ex> Sr
                              Biar<lb rend="hyphenated"/>na Þorsteinsson i vesterhops holum. <lb/>
                           Sr Biarne atti þetta kver f<ex>yrir</ex> 30. aru<ex>m</ex>
                           <lb/> og þadan fra til sins daudadags.</q> The note on the AM-slips
                        reads: <q xml:lang="is">Margretar Saga. <lb/> Mariu gratur (<foreign
                              xml:lang="la">er sermo de dolore. Mariæ, cum <lb/> filium Deum
                                 crucifi<lb rend="hyphenated"/>gi conspiceret. <lb/> Prosopopoeia
                              sub per<lb rend="hyphenated"/>sona Mariæ. <lb/> Precatio ad
                              Mariam</foreign>. <lb/> Þen<ex>n</ex>an<ex>n</ex> bækling feck <lb/>
                           eg 1708 af Pale <lb/> Jonssyni lgman<ex>n</ex>e <lb/> en<ex>n</ex>
                              han<ex>n</ex> af Sr Gud<lb rend="hyphenated"/>mundi Biarnasyne <lb/>
                           (prestz ad vestur<lb rend="hyphenated"/>hőps holum) ä Stad <lb/> i Hruta
                           firde. Sr <lb/> Gudmundur erfdi ep<lb/>ter fdur sin<ex>n</ex>,
                              en<ex>n</ex>
                           <lb/> Sr Biarne atte h<ex>an</ex>a, <lb/> þä Pall lgmadur <pb/> var hia
                              h<ex>onu</ex>m i ken<lb/>slu f<ex>iri</ex> 30. arum <lb/> Asmundur //
                           Sr Þorsteinn <lb/> i Vestur hops <lb/> holum Sr Þorb<ex>er</ex>gur <lb/>
                              k<ex>ir</ex>kiu p<ex>restur</ex> / <lb/> ä Holum <lb/> Sr Biarne i
                           vestur hops <lb/> holum.</q>
                     </p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>According to the AM-slips, <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni
                           Magnússon</name> acquired the codex from <foreign xml:lang="is"
                           >lögmaður</foreign>
                        <name type="person" key="PalJon005">Páll Jónsson vídalín</name> in <date
                           when="1708">1708</date>. See <ref type="ms" target="#AM04-0435-a-en">AM 435 a 4to</ref>, fol. 30v:
                           <q xml:lang="is">Eg feck þen<ex>n</ex>an bækling 1708. af lg<lb
                              rend="hyphenated"/>man<ex>n</ex>enum Ple Jonssyne.</q>, the AM-slip
                        has: <q xml:lang="is">Þen<ex>n</ex>an<ex>n</ex> bækling feck <lb/> eg 1708
                           af Pale <lb/> Jonssyni lgman<ex>n</ex>e</q>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
